==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sulphide
<hw>Sul"phide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A
binary compound of sulphur, or one so regarded; -- formerly called
<altname>sulphuret</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Double sulphide</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <cd>a
compound of two sulphides.</cd> -- <col><b>Hydrogen sulphide</b></col>.
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <cd>See under <er>Hydrogen</er>.</cd> --
<col><b>Metallic sulphide</b></col>, <cd>a binary compound of sulphur
with a metal.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sulphinate</ent>⟦br⟧
